  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH project in Boset  Adama districts, East Shewa Zone of Oromia Regional State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be implemented in Boset and Adama districts in East Shewa Zone of Oromia Region in order to alleviate the suffering of communities who are affected by the lack of potable water. It will prioritize those most vulnerable groups of people -children with a high degree of vulnerability- as primary beneficiaries, particularly malnourished children less than 5 years and pregnant and lactating women (PLW) &#x2013; in all stages of the project. The Boset and Adama WASH intervention will be executed through water trucking for highly affected community members for 21days, rehabilitation of six damaged boreholes, construction of three new boreholes, and promotion of public health and environmental sanitation. The project will be integrating gender throughout the interventions.

The project will be implemented over a six months&#x2019; period through mid 2016 as the hunger season is expected to extend for a protracted period. It will benefit 36,625 people directly and 35,909 people indirectly residing in the two districts. In addition to addressing the water shortage problem of the communities, it is also designed to support the enhancement of nutrition, health, hygiene and sanitation and education programs in the areas.</narrative>
  </description>
